If a confining unit is encountered, 6-inch PVC pipe outer casings will be installed and set 10 feet into the confining unit or to the bedrock, whichever is encountered first. All excavated spoils will be containerized in 55-gallon drums and sent for disposal upon review of chemical results. A dual tube Geoprobe™ sampling system will be utilized to drill all the borings, which consists of an outer steel tube which acts as a casing for the boring, and an inner sampling tube to prevent potential vertical migration of potential contaminants. The casing will be removed prior to abandoning each boring. Soil samples will be collected from each boring. The borings will be located within the bounds of the private property. The borings will be drilled utilizing 3.25-inch hollow stem, continuous flight augers. The borings will be performed utilizing a Truck-mounted drill rig and will generate an approximate 6-inch annulus.
